caption: Table 1: Prediction errors of different methods.
description: This table presents the prediction error (RMSE) results on a test set for various methods, including AIR, LRMR, TRLasso, DKN, and ViT, across different levels of model individualization (DI) and experimental conditions (Case 1 and Case 2).  The numbers represent the average RMSE and its standard error over 100 repetitions.  Case 1 and Case 2 represent different correlation structures between image blocks in the input data.  Lower RMSE values indicate better performance.

caption: Table 2: Prediction errors of different methods.
description: This table presents the prediction errors (RMSE) of five different methods: AIR, LRMR, TRLasso, DKN, and ViT, on a real-world ADNI dataset.  The results are averages across 5-fold cross-validation, with standard errors in parentheses.  The table demonstrates the superior performance of the proposed AIR method.
